The speed \(v\) of the muon can be obtained directly from

\[
v=\frac{\text{distance}}{\text{time}}
\]

where the distance the muon travels is \(d = 1000 \ \text{m}\) and the lifetime (time) is \(\tau = 2\times10^{-6}\ \text{s}\).

\[
v = \frac{1000\ \text{m}}{2\times10^{-6}\ \text{s}}
   = \frac{1000}{2\times10^{-6}}
   = 5\times10^{8}\ \text{m/s}
\]

So the muon moves at \(5 \times 10^{8}\) meters per second.

